HEADWORD: Branchial
<hw>Bran"chi*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to branchi⟦ae⟧ or gills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Branchial arches</b></col>, <cd>the bony or cartilaginous
arches which support the gills on each side of the throat of fishes and
amphibians. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</cd> --
<col><b>Branchial clefts</b></col>, <cd>the openings between the
branchial arches through which water passes.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
